cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DM, cs.SE

The paper deals with optimization problems using evolutionary algorithms, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of estimation of distribution algorithms and regularity-based models also suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the analysis of performance metrics and comparison experiments, which aligns with the sub-category of cs.DM (Data Mining). Finally, the use of diversity repairing mechanisms and dimension reduction techniques suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
